{{Infobox power station |name = Alvarado I |image = |image_caption = |location_map = Spain | coordinates = {{coord|38|49|37|N|06|49|34|W|region:ES-BA_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |country = Spain |location = [[Alvarado, Extremadura|Alvarado]], [[Province of Badajoz|Badajoz]] |owner = [[Acciona Energy]] |status = O |th_fuel_secondary = [[natural gas]] (backup) |th_combined_cycle = | solar_type = CSP | solar_csp_technology = P | solar_concentration = | solar_collectors = 768 | solar_collectors_area = | solar_site_area = | solar_site_resource = 2,174 kWh/m<sup>2</sup>/yr | ps_electrical_capacity = 50 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_storage_hours = | ps_annual_generation= 105.2 [[GWh]] | commissioned = July 2009 | decommissioned = }}
'''Alvarado I''' is a large [[solar thermal energy|solar thermal]] power station in [[Alvarado, Extremadura|Alvarado]], [[province of Badajoz]], in [[Extremadura]], [[Spain]]. Construction on the plant commenced in December 2007 and was completed in July 2009, when commercial operations began. With an installed capacity of {{nowrap|50 [[Megawatt|MWe]]}},<ref name="NREL">{{Citation |title=Alvarado I Solar Power Project |url= http://www.nrel.gov/csp/solarpaces/project_detail.cfm/projectID=5 |date=April 30, 2009 |publisher=[[National Renewable Energy Laboratory]] (NREL), [[U.S. Department of Energy]] |accessdate=2010-05-28}}</ref> it is one of the largest [[List of solar thermal power stations|solar thermal power stations]] in the world.<ref name="Annual Report">{{Citation |title=Acciona Energy: Annual Report 2008 |url=http://annualreport2008.acciona.com/media/61324/Acciona_energy(pdf).pdf |format=PDF |page=12 |accessdate=2010-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707075946/http://annualreport2008.acciona.com/media/61324/Acciona_energy(pdf).pdf |archive-date=2011-07-07 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Acciona Reports #43 |url=http://www.acciona.com/media/200346/acciona_reports_43.pdf |format=PDF |page=6 |accessdate=2010-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917065009/http://acciona.com/media/200346/acciona_reports_43.pdf |archive-date=2010-09-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
The facility is built on a {{Convert|1|km2|mi2|1|abbr=on}} site with a solar resource of {{nowrap|2,174 [[KWh]]/m<sup>2</sup>/year}}, producing an estimated {{nowrap|105,200 [[MWh]]}} of electricity per year (an average power of 12&nbsp;MW). The plant uses [[parabolic trough]] technology, and is made up of 768 [[solar thermal collector]]s, with an output temperature of {{Convert|393|C|F|0|abbr=on}}, transferred with [[Biphenyl]] and [[Diphenyl oxide]] heat transfer agents.<ref name="NREL"/>
A second {{nowrap|50 MWe}} facility, '''Alvarado II''', is currently on the proposal stage. It is planned to be constructed in the same area as Alvarado I.<ref name="Annual Report"/>
