{{Infobox company | name = Crnogorski elektroprenosni sistem AD | logo = CGES logo.svg | caption = | type = Joint-stock company | traded_as = [[Montenegro Stock Exchange|MNSE]]: [http://mnse.me/code/navigate.asp?Id=14&stockId=999 PREN] | fate = | predecessor = Prenos AD | successor = | foundation = {{Start date|2009}} | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Podgorica]] | location_country = [[Montenegro]] | locations = | area_served = [[Montenegro]] | key_people = Ivan Bulatovic ([[CEO]]) | industry = Electricity | products = | services = [[Electric power transmission]] | revenue = 28,874,175 € | operating_income = | net_income = 2,448,732 € | assets = 254,329,057 € | equity = | owner = [[Government of Montenegro]] (55%) [[Terna Group]] (22.08%) [[Elektromreža Srbije]] (10.01%) | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|http://www.cges.me/en/|http://www.cges.me/}} | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Crnogorski Elektroprenosni Sistem AD''' ([[Montenegro Stock Exchange|MNSE]]: [http://www.mnse.me/code/navigate.asp?Id=87&stockId=999 PREN]) ('''CGES'''; former name '''Prenos AD'''; meaning: '''Montenegrin Electrical Transmission System''') is an electric power [[transmission system operator]] located in [[Podgorica]], [[Montenegro]]. It is a member of [[European Network of Transmission System Operators for Electricity]]. '''[[AD (disambiguation)|AD]]''' stands for [[Akcionersko Drustvo]], or [[Joint Stock Company]].
In 2009, the company broke away from [[Elektroprivreda Crne Gore|EPCG]] and partly privatized, with 43.7% stake in the company acquired by the Italian utility company [[A2A]]. 22% stake is owned by Italian electricity transmission company [[Terna (Italian company)|Terna]].<ref name=levante260811> {{cite news | url = http://www.levanteonline.net/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4809:costruzione-del-cavo-elettrico-che-colleghera-litalia-al-montenegro-tra-polemiche-e-vantaggi-economici&catid=108:europa&Itemid=542 | archive-url = https://archive.is/20130221185349/http://www.levanteonline.net/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4809:costruzione-del-cavo-elettrico-che-colleghera-litalia-al-montenegro-tra-polemiche-e-vantaggi-economici&catid=108:europa&Itemid=542 | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2013-02-21 | title = Costruzione del cavo elettrico che collegherà l'Italia al Montenegro: tra polemiche e vantaggi economici |trans-title=Construction of the electrical cable to link Italy and Montenegro: controversies and economic benefits | language = Italian | work = il Levante | first = Valentina | last = Capozzi | date = 2011-08-26 | accessdate = 2012-04-11 }} </ref>
CGES and Terna are planning to build a {{convert|450|km|adj=on}} 1,000&nbsp;MW submarine cable between [[Tivat]] and [[Pescara]].<ref name=levante260811/><ref name=balkan051111> {{cite news | url = http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/the-underwater-cable | title =The Italy-Montenegro Cable | work = Balkan Insight | first = Nela | last = Lazarevic | date = 2011-11-05 | accessdate = 2012-04-11}} </ref> The cable to be operational by 2015.
The [[European Bank for Reconstruction and Development]] is preparing a €65&nbsp;million syndicated loan for the company. The loan would be used for the construction of a new substation at Lastva, and a new line from Lastva to [[Pljevlja]] to be connected to the Italy–Montenegro interconnector.<ref name=bloomberg240212> {{cite news | url = http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-02-24/ebrd-considers-eu65-million-loan-to-fund-montenegro-power-line.html | title = EBRD Considers EU65 Million Loan to Fund Montenegro Power Line | first1 = Misha| last1 = Savic | work = [[Bloomberg Businessweek]] | date = 2012-02-24 | accessdate = 2012-04-12}} </ref><ref name=balkans270212> {{cite news | url = http://www.balkans.com/open-news.php?uniquenumber=137164 | title = EBRD is considering EUR 65m loan for Crnogorski Elektroprenosni Sistem to upgrade Montenegro's power network | work = Balkans.com | agency = BNE | date = 2012-02-27 | accessdate = 2012-04-12}} </ref>
