'''Diablo Foothills Regional Park''' is a {{convert|1,060|acre|km2}} [[regional park]] of the [[East Bay Regional Park District]]. It is located in [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa County]], in the [[East Bay (San Francisco Bay Area)|East Bay region]] of northern [[California]].

==Geography==
The park lies in the Diablo Foothills of the northern [[Diablo Range]], west of [[Mount Diablo]] and [[Mount Diablo State Park]]. The closest city is [[Walnut Creek, California|Walnut Creek]]. 

Diablo Foothills Regional Park is bordered by: [[Castle Rock Park|Castle Rock Regional Recreation Area]] on the east, and Shell Ridge Open Space to the north. Together, these three parks provide {{convert|18000|acre|km2}} of parkland for visitors to enjoy. 

