'''Gottelborn Solar Park''' ({{lang-de|Solarpark Zeche Göttelborn}}) is a 8.4-[[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> [[photovoltaic power station]] located in [[Göttelborn]], in [[Quierschied]] municipality, Germany. The power plant was constructed by [[City Solar]] in two stages. The first stage was completed in August, 2004, followed by the second stage three years later in November 2007.<ref name="pvresources">[http://www.pvresources.com/en/top50pv.php World's largest photovoltaic systems] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071212195222/http://www.pvresources.com/en/top50pv.php |date=December 12, 2007 }}</ref>

The first stage of the plant includes 23,500 [[solar module]]s from the French manufacturer "Photowatt" at an estimated efficiency of 14%, with a nominal power output of 4&nbsp;MW<sub>p</sub><ref =epia">[http://www2.epia.org/member_area/m04NewsBoardSecretariat/NewsBoardSecretariat_newstyle.asp?c_year=2004&c_month=09&c_cat=5#815 EPIA - Newsletter<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and occupies a total area of {{convert|50000|m2|ft2|0}}<ref name="city solar pdf">http://www.city-solar-ag.com/fileadmin/templates/images/downloads/ENGLISH%20CS%20Referenzen.pdf</ref> The construction of the second stage required another 50,000 PV modules.<ref name="city solar">[http://www.city-solar-ag.com/index.php?id=77#3245 City Solar AG: Press releases] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071109174737/http://www.city-solar-ag.com/index.php?id=77#3245 |date=November 9, 2007 }}</ref>

