{{Infobox power station | name = Lassajavre Power Station | name_official = ''Lassajavre kraftverk'' | image = | location_map = Troms | location_map_caption = Location in [[Troms]] county | coordinates = {{coord|69|39|38|N|22|13|12|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Kvænangen]], [[Troms]] | country = Norway | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date and age|1977}} | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = Kvænangen Kraftverk AS | operator = | psps_upper_res = Lake Abo | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = Lake Lassa | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = | psps_generators = 1 × 7.2&nbsp;MW | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = [[Francis turbine]] | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 7.2 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 47.6%<!-- 30,000 MWh/year / ( 7.2 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.476 --> | ps_annual_generation = 30 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Lassajavre Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Lassajavre kraftverk}} or ''Lassajavrre kraftverk''<ref name="Hamnaberg">Hamnaberg, Håvard (ed.). 2011. ''Pumpekraft i Noreg: Kostnadar og utsikter til potensial'' (= Report no. 22). Oslo: Noregs vassdrags- og energidirektorat, p. 23ff.</ref>) is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Kvænangen]] in [[Troms]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref name="Hamnaberg"/> The plant utilizes a drop between Lake Abo ({{lang-fkv|Aapujärvi}}, {{lang-se|Ábojávri}})<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/5595 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Aapujoki.]</ref> and Lake Lassa ({{lang-fkv|Lassojärvi}}, {{lang-se|Lássájávri}}).<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/5830 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Lassojärvi.]</ref> Lake Abo is regulated at a level between {{convert|689|m|sp=us}} and {{cvt|669|m}}, and Lake Lassa serves as the reservoir for the [[Småvatna Hydroelectric Power Station]]. The Lassajavre plant also utilizes water from Lake Mollis ({{lang-fkv|Mollisjärvi}}, {{lang-se|Stuora Mollešjavri}})<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/6617 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Mollisjärvi.]</ref> and Lake Sarves ({{lang-fkv|Kolmas Hirvasjärvi}}, {{lang-se|Sarvvesjávri}}).<ref>[http://www.kvenskestedsnavn.no/stedsnavn/view/5777 Kvensk stedsnavndatabase: Kolmas Hirvasjärvi.]</ref> The plant came into operation in 1977.<ref name="Hamnaberg"/> It has a [[Francis turbine]] and operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|7.2 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, with an average annual production of about 30&nbsp;GWh.<ref name="Hamnaberg"/> The plant is controlled by Kvænangen Kraftverk AS, with a 48.2% share owned by Troms Kraft.<ref>[http://www.tromskraft.no/om/selskap/tkp/kraftverk Troms Kraft: Våre kraftverk.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119040058/http://www.tromskraft.no/om/selskap/tkp/kraftverk |date=2015-11-19 }}</ref>
