[[Image:Smoky Hills Wind Farm.jpg|right|thumb|The Smoky Hills Wind Farm as seen from Interstate 70]] The '''Smoky Hills Wind Farm''' (Phase I & Phase II) is a 250 [[megawatt]] (MW) [[wind farm]] in [[Lincoln County, Kansas|Lincoln]] and [[Ellsworth County, Kansas|Ellsworth Counties]], 140 miles west of Topeka in [[Kansas]], north of [[Ellsworth, Kansas|Ellsworth]]. The farm is operated by [[Enel Green Power]].<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.enelgreenpower.com/en-GB/plants/projects/smoky_hills/ |title = Wind: the 155 wind turbines at''' Smoky Hills |publisher = [[Enel Green Power]] |accessdate = 2010-11-04 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20101215021621/http://www.enelgreenpower.com/en-GB/plants/projects/smoky_hills/ |archivedate = 2010-12-15 |df = }}</ref> Highway [[K-14 (Kansas highway)|K-14]] and [[Interstate 70]] pass through parts of the wind farm, with clear views of many of the wind turbines.<ref name="carpenter_2007">{{Cite web |url=http://www.cjonline.com/stories/100707/loc_206025299.shtml |title=Energy farms are increasingly dotting Kansas' landscape |first=Tim |last=Carpenter |publisher=[[The Topeka Capital-Journal]] |date=2007-08-07 |accessdate=2009-01-02 }}</ref> The project uses 56 [[Vestas]] V80 1.8 MW [[wind turbines]]<ref name="awea_projects_kansas"/> and produces enough electricity to power some 37,000 average Kansas homes annually.<ref name="smoky_hills_I_open">{{Cite web |url=http://www.renewableenergyworld.com/rea/news/story?id=51677 |title=Smoky Hills I Wind Farm Open |publisher=Renewable Energy World |date=2008-02-27 |accessdate=2009-01-01 }}</ref> {{as of|2008|11|19}}, phase II is under construction with 99 [[GE 1.5 MW wind turbine]]s for an additional 148.5 MW,<ref name="awea_projects_kansas">{{Cite web|url=http://www.awea.org/projects/Projects.aspx?s=Kansas |title=U.S. Wind Energy Projects - Kansas |publisher=[[American Wind Energy Association]] |date=2008-11-19 |accessdate=2009-01-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081118074931/https://www.awea.org/projects/Projects.aspx?s=Kansas |archivedate=November 18, 2008 }}</ref> to bring the total [[nameplate capacity]] to 249.3 MW.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/business/1271826/enel_completes_smoky_hills_wind_project_in_kansas/index.html |title=Enel Completes Smoky Hills Wind Project in Kansas |publisher=RedOrbit |date=2008-02-27 |accessdate=2009-01-01 }}</ref> Phase II was completed and began commercial operation in December 2008.<ref name="">{{Cite web |url=http://www.tradewindenergy.com/Project.aspx?id=220 |title=TradeWind Energy: Smoky Hills Wind Project Phase II |publisher=TradeWind Energy |date=n.d. |accessdate=2013-11-09 }}</ref>
